image_analysis.description: A photograph of a narrow hallway. The floor features a black and white checkerboard pattern. On the left wall, there is a large white canvas with vertical gray/brown line patterns. The ceiling is a standard drop-ceiling with square tiles and rectangular fluorescent light fixtures. Further down the hallway, there are stacked cardboard boxes, one of which has 'Crate & Barrel' branding visible. A door is visible at the far end of the corridor.
image_analysis.layout: Perspective shot looking down a hallway

stamps_or_markings: Bates stamp 'EFTA00000410' in bottom right corner

notes: The text 'Crate & Barrel' is partially obscured on a box in the background. The primary text is the Bates stamp identifier.
